<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,733,1406]" pageId="31" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,432,841,866]" pageId="31" pageNumber="191">Modified diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body with furry coat of cuticular setules and scattered spine-like, bifid setae. Pereonite 
<number box="[1422,1436,841,865]" pageId="31" pageNumber="191" value="3.0">3</number>
posterolateral margins produced posteriorly. Pereonite 
<number box="[767,781,877,901]" pageId="31" pageNumber="191" value="4.0">4</number>
width subequal pereonite 
<number box="[1078,1092,877,901]" pageId="31" pageNumber="191" value="5.0">5</number>
width, lateral margins curved; posterolateral margins rounded, not produced posteriorly, posterolateral setae present. Pereonite 
<number box="[1257,1271,913,937]" pageId="31" pageNumber="191" value="6.0">6</number>
length clearly larger pereonite 
<number box="[343,357,949,973]" pageId="31" pageNumber="191" value="5.0">5</number>
length. Female pleotelson ovoid, waist absent. Pereopod III ischium dorsal lobe triangular. Pereopod VII length smaller pereopod VI length. Operculum elongate, length exceeding 
<number box="[1147,1182,985,1009]" pageId="31" pageNumber="191" value="1.5">1.5</number>
width.
</paragraph>
